    <span class="uppercase tracking-widest text-[10px] font-['Space_Grotesk'] text-[#bdf4ff] mb-2 block">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[14px] align-middle mr-1">shield</span>PERSONNEL FILE
    </span>
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold font-['Space_Grotesk'] uppercase tracking-widest text-[#dfe2eb] drop-shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(215,223,33,0.5)]">About UFO Hunters</h2>
  </div>

  <!-- Quote Block -->
  <div class="mb-10 bg-[#0a0e14] rounded-xl p-6 border-l-4 border-[#D7DF21]">
    <blockquote class="italic text-[#c9c8ad] leading-relaxed">
      <p>An unidentified flying object, or UFO, in its most general definition, is any apparent anomaly in the sky (or near or on the ground, but observed hovering, landing, or departing into the sky) that is not readily identifiable as any known object or phenomenon by visual observation and/or use of associated instrumentation such as radar. These anomalies were referred to popularly as "flying saucers" or "flying discs" during the late 1940s and early 1950s."</p>
      <footer class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest font-['Space_Grotesk'] text-[#bdf4ff] mt-4">Wikipedia definition of UFO</footer>
    </blockquote>
  </div>

  <!-- Mission Statement -->
  <div class="mb-10">
    <p class="text-[#dfe2eb] leading-relaxed">That is the wikipedia's definition of Unidentified Flying Object. <strong class="text-[#D7DF21]">ufo-hunters.com</strong> collects a huge data set of sightings all over the world. Our main purpose is to collaborate spreading <strong class="text-[#dfe2eb]">objective UFO data</strong>. We thank the work of organizations such as <a href="http://www.nuforc.org/" target="_blank" class="text-[#bdf4ff] hover:text-[#D7DF21] transition-colors">NUFORC</a> and <a href="http://www.mufon.com/" target="_blank" class="text-[#bdf4ff] hover:text-[#D7DF21] transition-colors">MUFON</a> that collect and investigate sighting reports and are a source of inspiration for us.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Founders Section -->
